{"id": 4045, "date": "2018-08-28T05:00:09", "date_gmt": "2018-08-28T12:00:09", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=4045"}, "modified": "2019-04-14T14:38:40", "modified_gmt": "2019-04-14T21:38:40", "slug": "meeting-across-the-river-darlene-love-and-bruce-springsteen-zip-a-dee-doo-dah", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2018/08/28/meeting-across-the-river-darlene-love-and-bruce-springsteen-zip-a-dee-doo-dah/", "title": {"rendered": "Meeting Across the River: Darlene Love and Bruce Springsteen, Zip-a-Dee-Doo-Dah"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>You might be more familiar with &#8220;Zip a Dee Doo Dah&#8221; in its original Disney incarnation, but in 1963, it went all the way to #8 on the charts when Bob B. Soxx and The Blue Jeans covered it. And if you&#8217;re not familiar with that\u00a0 band, you&#8217;re probably familiar with their featured vocalist on the track: Darlene Love.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/PWOkSyR_NhU?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p>In 2011, Darlene Love was inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame, and &#8220;Zip a Dee Doo Dah&#8221; was among the songs she performed at the induction ceremony.</p>\n<p>Bruce showed up to play lead guitar for Darlene (and that&#8217;s Curtis King on backing vocals)&#8211;resulting in one-off performance of an unexpected cover.</p>\n<div class=\"jetpack-video-wrapper\"><span class=\"embed-youtube\" style=\"text-align:center; display: block;\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" class=\"youtube-player\" width=\"758\" height=\"427\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/a2mjTLH5m38?version=3&#038;rel=1&#038;showsearch=0&#038;showinfo=1&#038;iv_load_policy=1&#038;fs=1&#038;hl=en-US&#038;autohide=2&#038;wmode=transparent\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" style=\"border:0;\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-presentation\"></iframe></span></div>\n<p><strong>Zip-a-Dee-Doo-Dah<br />\nFirst performed:</strong> March 14, 2011 (New York City, NY)<br />\n<strong>Last performed:</strong> March 14, 2011 (New York City, NY)</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>Bruce celebrates Darlene Love&#8217;s induction into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame by joining her on her 1963 hit.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 4211, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_mi_skip_tracking": false, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false, "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_is_tweetstorm": false, "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": []}, "categories": [4, 5], "tags": [1532, 547, 1510, 1531], "jetpack_publicize_connections": [], "aioseo_notices": [], "jetpack_featured_media_url": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/zipadee.jpg?fit=500%2C500&ssl=1", "jetpack_sharing_enabled": true, "jetpack_shortlink": "https://wp.me/p9w3Lk-13f", "jetpack_likes_enabled": true, "jetpack-related-posts": [{"id": 5725, "url": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2018/11/12/matr-darlene-love-bruce-springsteen-and-the-cbs-orchestra-today-i-met-the-boy-im-gonna-marry/", "url_meta": {"origin": 4045, "position": 0}, "title": "MatR: Darlene Love and Bruce Springsteen, Today I Met the Boy I&#8217;m Gonna Marry", "date": "November 12, 2018", "format": false, "excerpt": "One time only: Bruce joined Darlene Love at her Rock and Roll Hall of Fame induction, teaming up on \"Today I Met the Boy I'm Gonna Marry.\"", "rel": "", "context": "In &quot;Cover Me&quot;", "img": {"alt_text": "", "src": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/t_darlene_love__today_i_met_the_boy_im_gonna_marry_ic001_122.jpg?fit=400%2C376&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200", "width": 350, "height": 200}, "classes": []}, {"id": 29804, "url": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2021/10/02/matr-darlene-love-bette-midler-and-bruce-springsteen-hes-a-rebel/", "url_meta": {"origin": 4045, "position": 1}, "title": "MatR: Darlene Love, Bette Midler, and Bruce Springsteen: He&#8217;s a Rebel", "date": "October 2, 2021", "format": false, "excerpt": "One time only: Watch Bruce Springsteen back Darlene Love and Bette Midler on Love's greatest (yet uncredited) hit.", "rel": "", "context": "In &quot;Cover Me&quot;", "img": {"alt_text": "", "src": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/hesarebel.jpg?fit=1200%2C1200&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200", "width": 350, "height": 200}, "classes": []}, {"id": 6804, "url": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2019/01/02/matr-bruce-springsteen-and-darlene-love-da-doo-ron-ron/", "url_meta": {"origin": 4045, "position": 2}, "title": "MatR: Bruce Springsteen and Darlene Love, Da Doo Ron Ron", "date": "January 2, 2019", "format": false, "excerpt": "It's up for debate whether Darlene Love's vocals are anywhere to be found on the original recording, but she certainly was front and center with the E Street Band at the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame concert in 2009.", "rel": "", "context": "In &quot;Cover Me&quot;", "img": {"alt_text": "", "src": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/dadooronron.jpg?fit=1000%2C1000&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200", "width": 350, "height": 200}, "classes": []}, {"id": 42275, "url": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2023/03/14/kingdom-of-days-march-14-2/", "url_meta": {"origin": 4045, "position": 3}, "title": "Kingdom of Days: March 14", "date": "March 14, 2023", "format": false, "excerpt": "What's the big highlight on a day like this? Hall of Fame performances with U2 and Darlene Love? Guest appearances with Robert Gordon and Conor Oberst? A pristinely recorded 1972 rehearsal? You decide--there's too many to chose from.", "rel": "", "context": "In &quot;Kingdom of Days&quot;", "img": {"alt_text": "", "src": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/The-Early-Uber-Collection-Front.jpg?fit=800%2C685&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200", "width": 350, "height": 200}, "classes": []}, {"id": 7166, "url": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2019/01/28/cover-me-a-fine-fine-boy/", "url_meta": {"origin": 4045, "position": 4}, "title": "Cover Me: A Fine Fine Boy", "date": "January 28, 2019", "format": false, "excerpt": "Thirty-three years after he first covered it in concert, Bruce joins Darlene Love on stage for one of her greatest hits. Listen to both performances inside.", "rel": "", "context": "In &quot;Cover Me&quot;", "img": {"alt_text": "", "src": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/darlene-lovedef.png?fit=1200%2C1200&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200", "width": 350, "height": 200}, "classes": []}, {"id": 20490, "url": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2020/08/27/cover-me-shes-sure-the-girl-i-love/", "url_meta": {"origin": 4045, "position": 5}, "title": "Cover Me: She&#8217;s Sure the Girl I Love", "date": "August 27, 2020", "format": false, "excerpt": "One time only: Bruce covers Darlene Love (in a song for which she was never credited) for the first time in the summer of 1976.", "rel": "", "context": "In &quot;Cover Me&quot;", "img": {"alt_text": "", "src": "https://i0.wp.com/estreetshuffle.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/crystals-hes-sure-the-boy-i-love.jpg?fit=754%2C768&ssl=1&resize=350%2C200", "width": 350, "height": 200}, "classes": []}], "_links": {"self": [{"href": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/wp-json/wp/v2/posts/4045"}], "collection": [{"href": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/wp-json/wp/v2/pos